    <h2><%: Title %>.</h2>
    <p>
        <span>We know&nbsp;getting your car serviced is one of those ‘grudge purchases’ and at the bottom of your shopping list but here’s what else we know – getting your car serviced regularly is necessary and could save you in the long run! Not only does it ensure that your car is kept in tip-top condition, keeping you and your family safe, but a regular small expense is much easier on the bank balance than a large unexpected one.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p>
    <span>See, if you don’t regularly care for your car’s health you might have a whopper of a pay out later on a much bigger mechanical fault that could have been caught through regular servicing (and at a lower cost!). Not only that – a car’s resale value can even be reduced if it doesn’t come with a ‘full service history,’ meaning an assurance that the car was serviced regularly and as specified by the manufacturer.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p>
    <strong><span>Have we convinced you? Regular servicing really is important for your safety&nbsp;</span></strong><em><b><span>and</span></b></em><strong><span>&nbsp;your bank balance!</span></strong><span><o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p>
    <span>With that in mind, we want you to be clear on what all the technical language means when it comes to car servicing because we know it can be confusing. Often, going to a mechanic can be like going to foreign country if you aren’t familiar with the ins and outs of your vehicle and all the different terms.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p>
    <span>That’s why we have put together this helpful guide to e-CAR car servicing – so you can get more service savvy before coming in to see us!<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p>
    <span>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p>
    <strong><span>1.&nbsp; Petrol Servicing</span></strong><span><o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p>
    <span>Vehicles run on lots of fluid, like oil and fuel, to keep going– in the servicing world we call this ‘lubrication.’ Without proper lubrication, your engine can not run.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p>
    <span>On more recent model cars, some manufacturers recommend that the oil is changed only every 30,000km in petrol vehicles due to how much oil technology has advanced. Manufacturers know their vehicles best and that’s why at e-CAR Service we service cars according to the manufacturer’s recommendation, including using the oils and lubricants they specifically recommend.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p>
    <span>When it comes to petrol servicing e-CAR Service will service parts like oils, transmission lubricants, oil filters, air filters, fuel filters, etc and, as mentioned, all as according to the recommended specifics of the manufacturer. Which means you can drive away knowing your car has been lubricated to its optimum specifications!<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p>
    <span>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>
