<p>
    <strong><span>How it works:</span></strong><span><o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p>
    <span>Engaging reverse gear will activate the rear sensing system. The front system is activated when the ignition is turned on or when the speed is below 15 km/ h. The system beeps with increasing frequency as the object comes closer to the bumper and emits a constant beep when the object is 30 cm from the bumper. The sensing system starts from 1.20 m for the rear and 0.8 m for the front.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p>
    <strong><span>Major feature:</span></strong><span>&nbsp;The unique design and setup procedure of the interactive system ensures that the sensing range of all 4 sensors are identical, providing you with the most accurate and uniform sensing pattern across the entire width of the bumper. A feature that not all sensing system can boast!<o:p></o:p></span></p>
